Subtitle
16
17 TO AMEND THE LAW REGARDING THE ARKANSAS
18 SCHOOL FOR MATHEMATICS, SCIENCES, AND
19 THE ARTS; AND TO AMEND THE LAW RELATED
20 TO THE TUITION AND FEES PAID BY STUDENTS
21 ENROLLED IN THE ONLINE PROGRAMS.
22
23 BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF ARKANSAS:
24
25 SECTION 1. Arkansas Code ยง 6-42-304(c), concerning tuition and fees
26 paid by students attending the Arkansas School for Mathematics, Sciences, and
27 the Arts, is amended to read as follows:
28 (c)(1) Students who are residents of this state selected to attend the
29 school school's residential programs shall not be required to pay tuition,
30 fees, or room and board.
31 (2) Students who are residents of other countries selected to
32 attend the school shall pay the cost of tuition, fees, and room and board as
33 established by the Board of Trustees of the University of Arkansas.
34 (3) Students who are enrolled in the school's online programs
35 shall pay the cost of tuition and fees as established by the Board of
36 Trustees of the University of Arkansas.
